===Noun===
'''Brennschluss'''
# the moment in the trajectory of a [[rocket]] when the fuel burns out, after which it continues with its own momentum for some distance and then begins to succumb to gravity; [[all-burnt]], [[burn-out]]
#:*'''1973''': The white line, abruptly, has stopped its climb.  That would be fuel cutoff, end of burning, what’s their word…'''Brennschluss'''.  We don’t have one.  Or else it’s classified. — Thomas Pynchon, ''Gravity's Rainbow''

